{
  "texts": [
    "In addition to CWI 86942, this L3 haplotype segment, or parts thereof, were found in multiple bread wheat landraces collected between the 1920s and the 1930s (Extended Data Fig. 6d), Tajikistan with high Jaccard indices carry the same L3 introgression segments as bread wheat landraces from Georgia, indicating a common origin of the L3 haplotype blocks (Supplementary Table 18).",
    "d, Diagram of chromosome 1D in the wheat lines Chinese Spring, CDC Stanley and CWI 86942.",
    "Haplotype blocks corresponding to Ae.",
    "tauschii L1 are indicated in yellow, L2 is indicated in blue, and L3 is in orange.",
    "The black bars above the chromosome indicate the region shown in e. e, Diagram of a portion of the long arm of bread wheat chromosome 1D."
  ]
}